    <stitle>BATTERY - TYPES OF BATTERIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TYPES OF BATTERIES</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>There are basically three types of batteries currently being used in trucks: filler cap,
                semi-maintenance free, and maintenance free.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>FILLER CAP</title>
            <para>These are lead acid batteries with a high degree of antimony in the grid alloy. They require frequent
                servicing, especially the need for adding water. Water is added to the battery after removal of cell
                filler caps.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
